Historically, sampling for orthopterans in the Malay Peninsula (including Peninsular Malaysia and Singapore ) is not evenly distributed (
Tan et al ., 2017
). For the katydids (Tettigonioidea) from Peninsular Malaysia , considerably more material has been examined and more species have been described from the state of Pahang and other northern states of Peninsular Malaysia (e.g., Hebard, 1922 ;
Gorochov, 1998 a
, 1998b; Ingrisch, 1995 , 1998 ). Likewise, there was also concerted effort to document the orthopteran diversity in Singapore more recently (e.g., Tan, 2011 , 2012 , 2017; Tan & Ingrisch, 2014 ). Conversely, in the state of Johor (south of Peninsular Malaysia and north of Singapore ), far fewer information about the orthopteran species is available.

Morphological features were imaged with a Canon EOS 700D digital SLR camera with a macro photo lens MP-E 
65 mm
f/2.8 USM (1–5×). Canon Macro Twin Lite MT-24EX was also used for lighting and flash. Image editing was accomplished using Adobe Photoshop CC 2014 (Adobe Systems Incorporated, San Jose, CA, 
USA
). Measurements of dried-pinned specimen were made from images using ImageJ 1.51j8 (Wayne Rasband, Research Services Branch, National Institute of Mental Health, Bethesda, MD, 
USA
). The following abbreviations are used: BL = body length; BWL = body with wing length; 
PL
= pronotum length; TL = tegmen length; HWT = hind wing tail length (part of hind wing surpassing tegmen); HFL = hind femur length; HTL = hind tibia length.

